item.title: About me
item.author: interruptrequestio@gmail.com (Wes Carroll)
item.description: Hello, Visitor! My Name is Wes Carroll and I have been dabbling with computers in one form or another since the late 1980’s when my father brought home our first “IBM PC-Compatiable clone.” I thought that it was the most amazing thing in the world and I was hooked from day one. I remember he setup a program that would run when I hit g then enter and a whole list of games would appear on the screen.
